Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 31.25 / 6.25 / 20 / 6.25
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive, vectors

Epidemiological comments: Zones endemic and with cyclical occurrence of the disease where campaigns for vector control and vaccination of susceptible species are carried out. Paired tests are being made to rule out the presence of the disease after recent vaccination. Laboratory results pending. 4 animals at the Rio Iglesias outbreak tested positive for Venezuelan equine encephalomyelitis [VEE] [Note: According to the OIE's database, VEE has been reported as absent, last occurrence July 2010]

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; vaccination in response to the outbreak (s); disinfection/disinfestations; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone ; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; control of vectors; no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Gorgas Memorial Institute for Health Studies (Regional Reference Laboratory) / Equidae / IgM-capture ELISA / 3 Sep 2015 / Positive

Future reporting:
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

